<HL>
   Phillips Petroleum Discovery
</HL>
<DATE>
05/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3
</SO>
<CO>
   P APIA EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
PETROLEUM (PET)
</IN>
<LP>
   BARTLESVILLE, Okla. -- Phillips Petroleum Co. said a
natural-gas discovery in the Southern Gas Basin of the U.K.
North Sea flowed at a rate of 31.5 million cubic feet a day
from a depth of 12,113 feet.
   The company said the well is about 80 miles from shore in
a water depth of 95 feet. Phillips is the operator with a 35%
interest, and other partners include American Petrofina Inc.,
with a 34.26% interest.
</LP>
