<HL>
   South Korea Invests Abroad
</HL>
<DATE>
05/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)
</IN>
<LP>
   SEOUL, South Korea -- South Korean investment overseas in
the first four months of this year soared 92% to $219 million
from $114 million a year earlier, the finance ministry said,
citing a worsening domestic manufacturing environment because
of rising wages and growing labor unrest. The number of
projects rose to 118 from 72.
   South Korea's total overseas investments to date amount to
$2.1 billion in 1,282 projects. Investments outstanding,
adjusted for withdrawn projects, reached $1.6 billion in
1,009 projects.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In this year's first four months, $87 million was invested
in Southeast Asia, $65 million in North America and $25
million in Europe.
</TEXT>
