INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)
</IN>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Hong Kong's April trade deficit widened to
3.37 billion Hong Kong dollars (US$433 million) from HK$2.36
billion a year earlier due to a drop in domestic exports, the
government said.
   The trade deficit narrowed, however, from the shortfall of
HK$3.86 billion recorded in March.
</LP>
