</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.STA WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   Standard Chartered PLC, a major British bank based in
London, announced changes in senior management positions,
which will make Deputy Group Chief Executive Bill Brown a
group deputy chairman.
   The changes, to go into effect June 1, were made as part
of the bank's efforts to strengthen its banking and
fee-earning businesses. Geoffrey Williams, who retires as
deputy chairman of J. Henry Schroder Wagg in July, is to
become Standard's group executive director responsible for
merchant banking joint ventures with Westdeutsche Landesbank
Girozentrate.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   John MacKenzie, group executive director, merchant
banking, will have responsibility for the strategic
enhancement of fee income, expanding less asset-intensive
businesses and identifying new opportunities in financial
services, the company said.
   Chairman and Group Chief Executive of Standard Chartered,
Rodney Galpin, said the company wants to increase
management's focus on "banking operations and to intensify
efforts to generate fee-earning products and develop fee
earning businesses."
